## Planning Deliverables by Complexity Level

### Level 1 (Quick Fix)
- Problem definition
- Solution approach
- Affected code areas
- Testing plan

### Level 2 (Feature Enhancement)
- Feature requirements
- Design overview
- Task breakdown
- Testing approach
- Integration points

### Level 3 (Component Development)
- Detailed requirements
- Component architecture
- Interface definitions
- Comprehensive task plan
- Test strategy
- Risk assessment

### Level 4 (System Architecture)
- Comprehensive requirements documentation
- System architecture diagrams
- Detailed component designs
- Interface specifications
- Phased implementation plan
- Test strategy for all phases
- Performance considerations
- Security considerations
- Risk assessment and mitigation

## Planning Checklist

- [ ] Fully understand the task requirements
- [ ] Analyze existing code and architecture
- [ ] Determine task complexity level
- [ ] Document requirements appropriately for the level
- [ ] Create design documentation at appropriate detail
- [ ] Break down implementation into concrete tasks
- [ ] Plan testing approach
- [ ] Identify integration points and dependencies
- [ ] Assess potential risks
- [ ] Estimate time and effort
- [ ] Finalize implementation plan document
- [ ] Review plan with stakeholders if needed

## Transition to Creative Mode

Once planning is complete:
1. Ensure the implementation plan is clear and actionable
2. Verify all requirements are captured
3. Confirm the task breakdown is sufficiently detailed
4. Ensure risks are identified and mitigated
5. Transition to Creative Mode to explore implementation approaches and design solutions
